{"id":412602594,"lang":"python3","time":"8Â months, 1Â week","timestamp":1603550643,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"72 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/412602594/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Multiply Strings","memory":"14 MB","code":"from collections import defaultdict\n\nclass Solution:\n    def multiply(self, num1: str, num2: str) -> str:\n        if num1 == \"0\" or num2 == \"0\": return \"0\"\n        result = defaultdict(int)\n        num1 = [int(i) for i in num1][::-1]\n        num2 = [int(i) for i in num2][::-1]\n        \n        for i in range(len(num1)):\n            num = num1[i]\n            for j in range(i, i + len(num2)):\n                result[j] += num * num2[j - i]\n\n        ans = []\n        carry = 0\n        idx = 0\n        ln = len(result)\n        while idx < ln:\n            carry = result[idx] // 10\n            ans.append(result[idx] % 10)\n            result[idx + 1] += carry\n            idx += 1\n            if idx >= ln and carry != 0:\n                ln += 1\n        ans = [str(i) for i in ans]\n        return \"\".join(ans[::-1])","compare_result":"","title_slug":"multiply-strings"}
